The paper proposes a method to optimize t-SNE, a popular tool for embedding multi-dimensional datasets into two or three dimensions. The paper discusses the use of neural networks and unsupervised scenarios, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of t-SNE in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), indicating a potential focus on these sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of random projections, which is a common technique in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE).
